login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", LOGIN WITH USERNAME AND PASSWORD\n+const login = cred => {\n+  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+    let options = {\n+      method: 'POST',\n+      uri: djangoUrl +'/accounts/login/',\n+      header: {'content-type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'},\n+      form: cred,\n+      resolveWithFullResponse: true,\n+      json: true\n+    }\n+    \n+    let body;\n+    let encryptedPassword;\n+\n+    aes256.encrypt(cred.password).then(encrypted => {\n+      encryptedPassword = encrypted;\n+    })\n+    // SEND POST REQUEST TO LOGIN\n+    .then(() => {\n+      return request(options).then(response => {\n+        body = response.body;\n+        return response.headers['set-cookie'];\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error.error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // PARSE Set-Cookie HEADER INTO COOKIE OBJECTS\n+    .then(cookieStrings => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+\n+      for(cookieString of cookieStrings){\n+        promises.push(new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          resolve(cookie.parse(cookieString));\n+        }));\n+      }\n+\n+      return Promise.all(promises).then(cookies => {\n+        return cookies;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // SAVES USERNAME, PASSWORD, CSRF TOKEN, SESSION TOKEN IN OPERATING SYSTEM'S PASSWORD VAULT\n+    .then(cookies => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+      let expiry = 0;\n+\n+      promises.push(keytar.setPassword('Dietstory', body.name, encryptedPassword));\n+      for(cookieObject of cookies){\n+        if(cookieObject.hasOwnProperty('csrftoken')){\n+          csrfToken = cookieObject.csrftoken;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+          promises.push(keytar.setPassword('Dietstory_CSRF', body.name, cookieObject.csrftoken));\n+        }\n+        else if(cookieObject.hasOwnProperty('sessionid')){\n+          sessionKey = cookieObject.sessionid;  // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+          promises.push(keytar.setPassword('Dietstory_Session', body.name, cookieObject.sessionid));\n+          expiry = Date.parse(cookieObject.expires);\n+        }\n+      }\n+      \n+      return Promise.all(promises).then(() => {\n+        return expiry;\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // SAVE USER INFO FOR FUTURE AUTO-LOGIN TO USE (ENCRYPTED)\n+    .then(expiry => {\n+      let encrypt = string => {\n+        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          let cipher = crypto.createCipheriv(secret.algorithm, Buffer.from(secret.key, 'hex'), Buffer.from(secret.iv, 'hex'));\n+          let encrypted = cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+      let userInfo = {...body, session_expiry: expiry};\n+\n+      return encrypt(JSON.stringify(userInfo)).then(encyrptedData => {\n+        fs.writeFileSync(path.join(app.getPath('userData'), 'user_info'), encyrptedData, 'utf-8');\n+        return userInfo;\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // RETURNS DJANGO RESPONSE BODY\n+    .then(userInfo => {\n+      resolve({body: body, userInfo: userInfo});\n+    })\n+    .catch(error => {\n+      reject(error);\n+    });\n+  });\n+}\n+\n+\n+\n+\n+\n+\n+// AUTO LOGIN\n+const autoLogin = () => {\n+  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+    // READ AND DECRYPT user_info FILE\n+    fs.readFile(path.join(app.getPath('userData'), 'user_info'), 'utf-8').then(encryptedData => {\n+      let decrypt = data => {\n+        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          let encrypted = Buffer.from(data, 'hex');\n+          let decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv(secret.algorithm, Buffer.from(secret.key, 'hex'), Buffer.from(secret.iv, 'hex'));\n+          let decrypted = decipher.update(encrypted);\n+          decrypted = Buffer.concat([decrypted, decipher.final()]);\n+          resolve(decrypted.toString());\n+        })\n+      }\n+\n+      return decrypt(encryptedData).then(userInfo => {\n+        return JSON.parse(userInfo);\n+      })\n+    })\n+    // GET USER'S PASSWORD\n+    .then(userInfo => {\n+      return keytar.getPassword('Dietstory', userInfo.name).then(password => {\n+        return aes256.decrypt(password).then(decryptedPassword => {\n+          return {...userInfo, password: decryptedPassword};\n+        })\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // GET SESSION TOKEN\n+    .then(userInfo => {\n+      // SESSION IS EXPIRED, MUST RE-LOG\n+      if(Date.now() > userInfo.session_expiry){\n+        return login({username: userInfo.name, password: userInfo.password}).then(response => {\n+          return keytar.getPassword('Dietstory_Session', response.userInfo.name).then(sessionToken => {\n+            return {...response.userInfo, password: userInfo.password, session_token: sessionToken};\n+          });\n+        })\n+        .catch(error => {\n+          throw error;\n+        });\n+      }\n+      // SESSION IS STILL GOOD, RETRIEVE AND USE IT\n+      else{\n+        return keytar.getPassword('Dietstory_Session', userInfo.name).then(sessionToken => {\n+          if(sessionToken !== null){\n+            return {...userInfo, session_token: sessionToken};\n+          }\n+          else{\n+            throw new Error('Cannot find session token');\n+          }\n+        });\n+      }\n+    })\n+    // GET CSRF TOKEN\n+    .then(userInfo => {\n+      return keytar.getPassword('Dietstory_CSRF', userInfo.name).then(csrfToken => {\n+        if(csrfToken !== null){\n+          return {...userInfo, csrf_token: csrfToken};\n+        }\n+        else{\n+          throw new Error('Cannot find CSRF token');\n+        }\n+      });\n+    })\n+    .then(userInfo => {\n+      sessionKey = userInfo.session_token;      // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+      sessionExpiry = userInfo.session_expiry;  // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+      csrfToken = userInfo.csrf_token;          // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+\n+ "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790",      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // SAVE USER INFO FOR FUTURE AUTO-LOGIN TO USE (ENCRYPTED)\n+    .then(expiry => {\n+      let encrypt = string => {\n+ cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", })\n+    // PARSE Set-Cookie HEADER INTO COOKIE OBJECTS\n+    .then(cookieStrings => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+\n+      for(cookieString of cookieStrings){\n+        promises.push(new cookieObject.csrftoken;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+          promises.push(keytar.setPassword('Dietstory_CSRF', body.name, cookieObject.csrftoken));\n+        }\n+        else cookieObject.sessionid));\n+          expiry = Date.parse(cookieObject.expires);\n+        }\n+      }\n+      \n+      return Promise.all(promises).then(() => {\n+        return expiry;\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // SAVE USER INFO FOR FUTURE AUTO-LOGIN TO USE (ENCRYPTED)\n+    .then(expiry => {\n+      let encrypt = string => {\n+        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          let cipher = crypto.createCipheriv(secret.algorithm, Buffer.from(secret.key, 'hex'), Buffer.from(secret.iv, 'hex'));\n+          let encrypted = cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", })\n+    // PARSE Set-Cookie HEADER INTO COOKIE OBJECTS\n+    .then(cookieStrings => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+\n+      for(cookieString of cookieStrings){\n+        promises.push(new return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          let cipher = crypto.createCipheriv(secret.algorithm, Buffer.from(secret.key, 'hex'), Buffer.from(secret.iv, 'hex'));\n+          let encrypted = cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", })\n+    // PARSE Set-Cookie HEADER INTO COOKIE OBJECTS\n+    .then(cookieStrings => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+\n+      for(cookieString of cookieStrings){\n+        promises.push(new cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", LOGIN WITH USERNAME AND PASSWORD\n+const login = cred => {\n+  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+    let options = {\n+      method: 'POST',\n+      uri: djangoUrl +'/accounts/login/',\n+      header: {'content-type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'},\n+      form: cred,\n+      resolveWithFullResponse: true,\n+      json: true\n+    }\n+    \n+    let body;\n+    let encryptedPassword;\n+\n+    aes256.encrypt(cred.password).then(encrypted => {\n+      encryptedPassword = encrypted;\n+    })\n+    // SEND POST REQUEST TO LOGIN\n+    .then(() => {\n+      return request(options).then(response => {\n+        body = response.body;\n+        return response.headers['set-cookie'];\n+      })\n+      .catch(error => {\n+        throw error.error;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // PARSE Set-Cookie HEADER INTO COOKIE OBJECTS\n+    .then(cookieStrings => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+\n+      for(cookieString of cookieStrings){\n+        promises.push(new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          resolve(cookie.parse(cookieString));\n+        }));\n+      }\n+\n+      return Promise.all(promises).then(cookies => {\n+        return cookies;\n+      });\n+    })\n+    // SAVES USERNAME, PASSWORD, CSRF TOKEN, SESSION TOKEN IN OPERATING SYSTEM'S PASSWORD VAULT\n+    .then(cookies => {\n+      let promises = [];\n+      let expiry = 0;\n+\n+ cookieObject.csrftoken;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+          promises.push(keytar.setPassword('Dietstory_CSRF', body.name, cookieObject.csrftoken));\n+        }\n+        else cookieObject.sessionid));\n+          expiry = Date.parse(cookieObject.expires);\n+        }\n+      }\n+      \n+      return Promise.all(promises).then(() => {\n+        return expiry;\n+      })\n+ return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+          let cipher = crypto.createCipheriv(secret.algorithm, Buffer.from(secret.key, 'hex'), Buffer.from(secret.iv, 'hex'));\n+          let encrypted = cipher.update(string, 'utf8', 'hex');\n+          encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\n+          resolve(encrypted);\n+        });\n+      }\n+\n+      sessionExpiry = expiry;   // GLOBAL VARIABLE\n+ "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Rayden440/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "**Persistent login**\r\n\r\n- When user logs in the client saves their password, username, csrf token and session token in the operating system's password vault.\r\n- Then it encrypts the user info (username, email, is_active, is_superuser, session_expiry), and stores it in `user_info` file.\r\n- When the user closes the app and reopens it, the client pulls user info from the file and credentials/tokens from Credential Manager or KeyChain or Secret Service. Auto logs in with those info, if anything is missing auto login will fail and user must go back to typing username and password.\r\n- Created a request wrapper function to check if the session is expired. If the session is expired it will pull the username/password and automatically send login request to Django server. \r\n- Wrapper function also intercepts outbound request to Django server and injects `X-CSRFToken` and `Cookie: sessionid=<session_token>`into the request header. Skips this step if outbound request is not for Django server.\r\n- Logout now cleans up `user_info` file created by login, and deletes username, password, csrf token and session token from OS's password vault.", "created_at": "2019-12-15T06:09:01Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-17T16:59:45Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "4d7efc19415c8a54f90549c3b2e3eb6a53f0c790", Rewrote file hash comparison to use promises, thus making it easier to understand the asynchronous flow of the code. Also, code for making HTTP HEAD request has been added to the hash comparison function.\r\n2. Changed django server to send correct response and added an additional presigned URL for HEAD request.\r\n3. Now when user launches the app, it will check Windows Defender settings and see if the game installation path is excluded. If not then run a powershell command to add exclusion (requires superuser/admin privileges).\r\n4. After file comparison, electron will update React on whether the game is up to date or not. If it is not then we can emit the download difference event via `ipcRenderer`.\r\n5. Makes a `tmp` folder in `userData` directory to temporarily house the files that will be downloaded.\r\n6. Calculates total size of all the files to be downloaded.\r\n7. Download the file into the previously created `tmp` folder, calculating the MD5 hash as we receive the file.\r\n8. Copy files from `tmp` to `gameInstallationPath`.\r\n9. Updates local hash map.\r\n10. Cache local hash map for future usage.\r\n11. RETURNS MAP\n+calculateHashes = masterList =>{\n+  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n+    let calculatedList = new Map();\n+    let filesList = masterList.keys();\n+\n+    async.eachSeries(filesList, (file, callback) => {\n+      let stream = _fs.createReadStream(path.join(gameInstallationPath, file));\n+      let hash = crypto.createHash('md5');\n+      stream.on('data', chunk => {\n+        hash.update(chunk);\n+      });\n+      stream.on('error', error => {\n+        calculatedList.set(file, '');\n+        callback();\n+      });\n+      stream.on('end', () => {\n+        calculatedList.set(file, hash.digest('hex'));\n+        callback();\n+      });\n+    }, (error) => {\n+      resolve(calculatedList);\n+    });\n+  });\n+}\n+", Linux: `~/.config/Dietstory`\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen React request for an update check, the following occurs:\r\n\r\n1. Makes a HTTP GET request to Django for the list of file hashes of the latest version.\r\n2. Check if the user has their local Maplestory file hashes cached (`<USER DATA>/hash_cache.json`).\r\n3. i. IF the cache file exist use content as the user's local hashes.\r\n ii. ELSE, user must compute MD5 hash for every file in the list of files from the Django.\r\n4. Compare local hashes to server's hashes, push file name of difference to an array.\r\n5. IF local hashes differs from server hashes, user must update their game files.", "created_at": "2019-11-29T02:24:28Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-29T18:01:13Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null,
